the first settlers came to dayton from the connorsville-noblesville-strawtown area of  in 1825. william bush divided part of his land into lots about 1827. bush and dr. timothy horram filed adjoining town plats on the same day in 1829. then a few years later david gregory filed a third plat, and the combined town took the name of dayton after the principal town in the area of southern ohio from which many of the settlers came.